            . I was on duty as a constable in <placeName id="t18200918-207-crimeloc1198">St. James's-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-207-crimeloc1198" type="placeName" value="St. James's-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-207-crimeloc1198" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-207-off1196 t18200918-207-crimeloc1198"></join>, and saw the prisoner very active in the mob - he attempted a dozen different peoples' pockets. At last I saw him take a blue handkerchief from a gentleman's pocket, and as the Queen left the house, I followed him to Pall-mall, apprehended him, and took six handkerchiefs from him, one of which was that I saw him take I had told the gentleman of it, but he went away.</p>
               <p>
            
